,"Week 9 of embryonic development","Week 10 of embryonic development"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring \u003Cstrong\u003Eweek 7 of embryonic development\u003C/strong\u003E, the medial nasal processes fuse in the midline to form the intermaxillary segment. This structure develops into:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe philtrum of the upper lip\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe primary palate\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe premaxillary part of the maxilla\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe associated gum and teeth\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect timing options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWeek 6 of embryonic development\u003C/strong\u003E - This week marks the initial formation and growth of facial processes, but fusion has not yet occurred\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWeek 8 of embryonic development\u003C/strong\u003E - By this stage, the basic facial structure is already established\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWeek 9 of embryonic development\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eweek 10 of embryonic development\u003C/strong\u003E - These weeks involve further refinement and growth of facial structures, but the key fusion events have already occurred\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFailure of proper fusion of the medial nasal processes can result in midline facial defects such as median cleft lip.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The medial nasal processes fuse during week 7 of embryonic development to form the intermaxillary segment.","The intermaxillary segment gives rise to the philtrum of the upper lip, primary palate, and upper jaw components.","Proper fusion of medial nasal processes is critical to prevent midline facial defects."],"references":["Ansari A, Bordoni B. Embryology, Face. [Updated 2024 Jan 30]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK545202/","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences.","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58938"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16010"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58938","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58938"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-23T21:34:27+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-23T21:37:36+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8701"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73469"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroup